        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48670",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello monk e boy,\r\nyou never get the line number with the error:\r\n{code:title=INI-File}\r\ncms.paes.ntro.lael      = Edit\r\ncms.pags.intr.moule     = admin\r\ncm.pages.into.controler = cms\r\ncms.paes.intro.ation    = editor\r\n{code}\r\nThis is a correct file, because there is no error in the ini syntax! {{Zend_Config}} ({{parse_ini_file}}) works without problems.\r\n\r\nOnly if the ini syntax is wrong, then you get an error:\r\n{code:title=INI-File with wrong syntax}\r\ncms.pages.intro.label = Edit\r\n\r\n!\r\n{code}\r\n{code:title=Result|borderStyle=solid}\r\nFatal error: Uncaught exception 'Zend_Config_Exception' with message 'syntax error, unexpected '!' in foo.ini on line 3\r\n{code}\r\nSo you can see, there is no chance to get a line number, if no syntax error is present.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-11T15:24:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-11T15:24:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48678",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=monk.e.boy",
                        "name": "monk.e.boy",
                        "displayName": "monk e boy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\r\nFrom the example on: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.config.adapters.ini.html\r\n\r\nWhy can't I do:\r\n\r\n  $config = new Zend_Config_Ini('\/path\/to\/config.ini', 'staging');   \r\n  echo $config->database->params->host;   \/\/ prints \"dev.example.com\"\r\n  echo $config->database->params->dbname; \/\/ prints \"dbname\"\r\n  \/\/ PROPOSED CHANGES:\r\n  echo $config->database->params->host->meta;  \/\/ prints \"\/path\/to\/config.ini, line 44\"\r\n\r\nThen this could be used to fix the other bug linked in my first comment.\r\n\r\nmonk.e.boy\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=monk.e.boy",
                        "name": "monk.e.boy",
                        "displayName": "monk e boy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-12T15:41:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-12T15:41:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48679",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=monk.e.boy",
                        "name": "monk.e.boy",
                        "displayName": "monk e boy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, I should have mentioned that Zend_Config_Ini would have to save this info somewhere (or calculate it when it's needed)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=monk.e.boy",
                        "name": "monk.e.boy",
                        "displayName": "monk e boy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-12T15:43:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-12T15:43:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48680",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}{code}echo $config->database->params->host->meta;{code}{quote}\r\nPrints the error message:\r\n{code:title=Result|borderStyle=solid}\r\nNotice: Trying to get property of non-object in \/\u2026\/foo.php on line 9\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-12T16:30:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-12T16:30:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48690",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=monk.e.boy",
                        "name": "monk.e.boy",
                        "displayName": "monk e boy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\/\/ PROPOSED CHANGES:\r\necho $config->database->params->host->meta; \/\/ prints \"\/path\/to\/config.ini, line 44\"\r\n\r\nLook, it's not rocket science. Just store the file name and line number with each item in the Config. I propose the attribute in the config item is called 'meta' but feel free to call it what you like.\r\n\r\nAs an optimisation you could normalize the data a bit.\r\n\r\nmonk.e.boy",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=monk.e.boy",
                        "name": "monk.e.boy",
                        "displayName": "monk e boy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-14T09:16:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-14T09:16:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48691",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The current operation of Zend_Config is that $config->b doesn't generate any errors if b doesn't exit. (though $config->a->b will do as Frank notes). Any change to this behaviour has to be added as a configurable option as we cannot break B\/C on ZF 1.\r\n\r\nIf we are going to generate an error message on property not found, then it should be an Exception, not an echoed message.\r\n\r\nIf you have signed the CLA, please provide a patch that meets these criteria.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-14T09:23:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-14T09:23:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
